<TITLE> 4 BDR men 'fall ill', land in DMCH </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Apr 2 (bdnews24.com)Four under-custody BDR men were taken to DMCH late Thursday night for treatment "after they fell ill", police said. They said the four, on remand in the Feb mutiny case, were brought to the government hospital in pairs. Lalbagh thana ASI Abdul Hakim brought havildar Didar, 44, lance naik Delwar,41, at 9:30pm. Half an hour later, SI Zahirul Islam accompanied havilder Shahjalal, 52, and sepoy Saiful Islam, 22. Both police officers said these men fell ill at the Lalbagh thana. bdnews24.com DMCH correspondent said the four were limping as they came in, and admitted to Ward 31. "Their legs appeared swollen," the correspondent said. bdnew
